summary.title: SkyNav Threat Model
summary.owner: Piranavan Ratnarajah - RAT22528167 , Stephen Johnson - A00038610
summary.description: SkyNav -FlightPilot is a navigation tool for professional pilots that integrates real-time data and predictive analytics to improve situational awareness. It streamlines navigation, enabling faster, more informed decision-making and reducing flight time. With live data updates, FlightPilot helps pilots adapt to changing conditions efficiently. By simplifying navigation tasks, it allows pilots to focus more on critical aspects of the flight, enhancing safety and operational efficiency.

data.name: Pilot
data.description: Provides input and interacts with the system.

data.name: External Systems
data.description: External systems could include services or databases that interact with SkyNav for purposes like weather updates, traffic data, geolocation information, flight scheduling, or authentication services. These systems typically operate outside of SkyNav but are integrated to enhance functionality or provide necessary data for the operation of the system.
data.reasonOutOfScope: External Systems are out of scope because they do not belong to the core SkyNav navigation and control system. They provide external data (such as weather, air traffic, etc.) or services (like authentication), but they are not part of the flight management or control processes directly.

data.name: Navigation Module
data.description: Determines optimal paths and navigation decisions.

data.name: User Interface
data.description: Manages user interactions and displays system feedback.

data.name: Communication Module
data.description: Handles external communications with other systems.

data.name: Data Flow
data.description: Paths for data movement, connecting actors, processes, and stores.

data.name: Trust Boundary
data.description: Separates trusted internal components from external entities.
